storm2013.commands
Class EncoderDrive

java.lang.Object
  edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command
      storm2013.commands.EncoderDrive
All Implemented Interfaces:
NamedSendable, Sendable
public class EncoderDrive
extends Command

Drives a certain number of wheel rotations based on an encoder. The encoder values are supplied by the IDriveTrainEncoder, which is implemented by some other class to supply values in rotations. It then drives at the specified drive speed until until it reaches the goal.

Author:
evan1026

EncoderDrive

public EncoderDrive(double goal,
                    double driveSpeed,
                    IDriveTrainEncoder encoder,
                    double decelThreshold,
                    double stopThreshold)
Main constructor for the class. More could be created if it proves to be worthwhile, but for now, use this one.

Parameters:
goal - How far you want to go (use rotations for units, just to make a standard).
driveSpeed - The speed at which you want to travel (also in rotations).
encoder - The class that implements IDriveTrainEncoder.
decelThreshold - The threshold to determine when to start to decelerate.
stopThreshold - The threshold to determine when to stop the command.
